properties.Name: Kill Dry Earthflow
properties.notes: significant movement bewteen 2005 and 2009 (prob 2008 winter); affects only logging roads

properties.Name: Summit Springs Slide
properties.notes: Zhong analyzed this slide once before; road it impacts accesses a popular horse packer trailhead in the Snow Mountain wilderness; the slide is in the headwaters of Bear Creek which eventually parallels Bear Creek Campground

properties.Name: Elk Mountain Earthflow
properties.notes: Massive, active earthflow; intersects a major county road

properties.Name: Howard Lake Slide
properties.notes: intersects a main route and has a campground on it

properties.Name: Blue Slides
properties.notes: affects a foot trail and potentially a main route

properties.Name: Slides Glade Landslide
properties.notes: affects mainly aquatic resources but may someday intercept a hiking trail; we have the most movement data for this slide

properties.Name: Klamath_Salmon Earthslide
properties.notes: that affects occupied structures on private land, CA Hwy 96, and FS road 12N23

properties.Name: Grider Earthflow
properties.notes: typically moves during wet years affecting FS roads 46N66, and 46N66.3, as well as local fish habitat below.

properties.Name: Buckhorn_Middle Landslide
properties.notes: moves most wet years, only potential fish habitat is affected.

properties.Name: Klamath_Benjamin Earthflow
properties.notes: affects occupied structures on private land, CA Hwy 96, and FS road 17N16.

properties.Name: Ferry Point Landslide
properties.notes: historically affected CA Hwy 96 below, however in 1985 on million cubic yards of material was excavated from the feature, it has not shown evidence of moving since.

properties.Name: Klamath_Dillon Earthflow
properties.notes: moves most wet years affecting CA Hwy 96

properties.Name: Bluff Creek Landslide
properties.notes: blocked stream course below resulting in a stream diversion that removed CA Hwy 96
